{"title_page": "Vanessa Lachey", "text_new": "{{short description|American-Filipino actress, model, presenter, and beauty queen}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name  = Vanessa Lachey\n| image = Vanessa Minnillo 2009.jpg\n| caption = Lachey at the  ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' Magazine's 10th Annual Hot 100 Celebration, [[Santa Monica, California]] on May 13, 2009\n| birth_name = Vanessa Joy Minnillo\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1980|11|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Angeles City]], [[Pampanga]], [[Philippines]]\n| residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] U.S.\n| occupation   = Television personality, beauty queen, model, television host, actress\n| years_active = 1998\u2013present\n| title = [[Miss South Carolina Teen USA]] 1998<br/>[[Miss Teen USA 1998]]\n| competitions = [[Miss South Carolina Teen USA]] 1998<br/>(Winner)<br/>[[Miss Teen USA 1998]]<br/>(Winner)\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Nick Lachey]]|2011}}\n| children     = 3\n}}\n\n'''Vanessa Joy Lachey''' (''n\u00e9e'' '''Minnillo'''; born November 9, 1980)<ref name=tvg>{{cite web | url = http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/vanessa-lachey/bio/337770 | title= Vanessa Lachey | website= [[TV Guide|TVGuide.com]] | accessdate= July 15, 2014| archivedate=August 28, 2016 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160828183422/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/vanessa-lachey/bio/337770/}}</ref> is a Filipino-American television personality, beauty queen, [[fashion model]], television host and actress. She was  named [[Miss Teen USA]] in 1998. She has been a New York-based correspondent for ''[[Entertainment Tonight]]'' and hosted ''[[Total Request Live]]'' on [[MTV]]. She has starred in two network sitcoms, and has hosted various competition and reality shows through the 2010s and 2020s.\n\n== Early life ==\n\n=== 1980\u20131997 ===\nVanessa Joy Minnillo was born at USAF Clark Regional Medical Center in [[Angeles City]], [[Pampanga]], [[Philippines]].<ref name=\"birth\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1942-27158-1412-9?cc=1410394&wc=3MG4-GPX:25277601,25277602,25268203,25611501|title=Philippines, Civil Registration (Local), 1888-1983 Image Philippines, Civil Registration (Local), 1888-1983; pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1942-27158-1412-9|website=FamilySearch.org|accessdate=March 15, 2015}} {{subscription}}</ref> Her father, Vincent Charles Minnillo, is an American citizen from [[Cleveland, Ohio]] of [[Italian people|Italian]] and [[Irish people|Irish]] descent, while her mother, Helen Ramos Bercero, is from [[Manila, Philippines]].<ref name=\"parents' marriage\">{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1942-27264-19072-26?cc=1410394&wc=3M57-6TT:25277601,25277602,25431201,25590101|title=Philippines, Civil Registration (Local), 1888-1983 Image Philippines, Civil Registration (Local), 1888-1983; pal:/MM9.3.1/TH-1942-27264-19072-26 \u2014 FamilySearch.org|publisher=|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://beta.inquirer.net/common/print.php?index=2&story_id=71100&site_id=24&col=134 |title=Nepales, Ruben V; Pampanga-born Vanessa Minnillo going places; Philippine Daily Inquirer |access-date=2007-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080222153757/http://beta.inquirer.net/common/print.php?index=2&story_id=71100&site_id=24&col=134 |archive-date=2008-02-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20050206091924/http://www.filipinasmag.com/magazine/archive/vanessa.html Ayuyang, Rachelle Q; There's Something About Vanessa]</ref><ref>[http://www.maximonline.com/articles/index.aspx?a_id=%207307&src=RSSArticles \"Dressed To Kill\"]; ''Maxim'' Online</ref> Minnillo has an adopted brother who is two years older.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://movies.yahoo.com/movie/contributor/1809781592/bio |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071014185047/http://movies.yahoo.com/movie/contributor/1809781592/bio |url-status=dead |archive-date=2007-10-14 |title=Vanessa Minnillo Biography \u2013 Yahoo! Movies |publisher=Movies.yahoo.com |date=1980-11-09 |accessdate=2011-02-20 }}</ref> Her father moved the family frequently because of his service in the Air Force. She lived in [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]], [[California]], [[Nevada]], [[Florida]], [[Germany]] and [[Japan]] and attended eight different schools in nine years. Minnillo's parents separated in 1983 and were divorced in 1986.<ref name=\"People Biography\">{{cite magazine|author=Vanessa Minnillo |url=http://www.people.com/people/vanessa_minnillo/biography |title=Vanessa Minnillo Biography |magazine=People.com |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref>\n\nMinnillo's parents both remarried. She and her brother Vincent Jr. relocated to [[Turkey]] with their mother and new stepfather. By 1991, in the wake of [[Operation Desert Shield (Gulf War)#Operation Desert Shield|Operation Desert Shield]], they returned to their father's home, eventually settling in [[Charleston, South Carolina]], where Minnillo attended the Roman Catholic [[Bishop England High School]] and was a [[cheerleader]].<ref name=IMDBBio>[http://imdb.com/name/nm0591373/bio IMDb biography], accessed 2007-08-19</ref>{{Better source|date=September 2017}} From then on, she lived with her father and stepmother, Donna. She also attended Our Lady of the Assumption Catholic School, in [[San Bernardino, California]], for one year.\n\n===1998\u20132007===\nMinnillo was crowned [[Miss South Carolina Teen USA]] and went on to win the title [[Miss Teen USA]] in 1998, the first Miss Teen USA from [[South Carolina]] and also the first from South Carolina to be named the pageant's [[Miss Teen USA Special Awards#Miss Congeniality|Miss Congeniality]].\nShe was a host on [[MTV]]'s ''[[Total Request Live]]'' (''TRL'') from 2003 until 2007<ref>[http://www.eonline.com/news/article/index.jsp?uuid=8e5e663a-838a-40e6-9ac0-c3194ba3f37f Minnillo Says Tootles to TRL], accessed 2007-08-19</ref> and became a [[New York City]] correspondent for ''[[Entertainment Tonight]]'' in 2005. Minnillo hosted Miss Teen USA (2004) and co-hosted Miss Universe (2007).\n\nAfter leaving [[MTV]] and ''[[Entertainment Tonight]]'', Minnillo was featured in print and web-based advertising for BONGO Jeans' Spring/Summer 2007 collection.<ref>[http://www.tmz.com/2007/01/05/vanessa-flashes-her-bongo/ Vanessa Flashes Her BONGO{{spaced ndash}}TMZ.com{{spaced ndash}}Entertainment News, Celebrity Gossip and Hollywood Rumors<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\nShe has been spokeswoman for [[Flirt! Cosmetics]], a line she helped create which debuted in August 2007, in [[Kohl's]] department stores.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://offtherack.people.com/2007/03/flirt_like_vane.html |title=Vanessa Minnillo's New Gig: Makeup Designer!{{spaced ndash}}Off the Rack{{spaced ndash}}StyleWatch{{spaced ndash}}People.com<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2007-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070320130523/http://offtherack.people.com/2007/03/flirt_like_vane.html |archive-date=2007-03-20 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nIn May 2006, ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' magazine ranked Minnillo #15 in its annual Hot 100 issue.<ref>[http://www.maximonline.com/slideshows/index.aspx?slideId=1920&imgCollectId=94 Vanessa Minnillo of 2006 Hot 100 on Maxim.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> She has been featured on the covers of ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' (October 2005, October 2006), ''[[Shape Magazine|Shape]]'' (March 2007), and ''[[Lucky (magazine)|Lucky]]'' (July 2007).\n\n===2007\u2013present===\nLachey was a finalist in [[E!]]'s competition to replace [[Brooke Burke]] as host of ''[[Wild On!]]''.<ref name=\"People Biography\"/> She also hosted ''[[True Beauty (TV series)|True Beauty]]'', a competition in which 10 contestants vie for $100,000 and inclusion in [[People Magazine]]'s 100 Most Beautiful People issue. The series premiered on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] on January 5, 2009, with a first season that ran through February 23, 2009. ABC renewed the series for a second season which ran from May 31, 2010 through July 19, 2010.\nLachey became a co-host of ABC's [[Wipeout (2008 U.S. game show)|''Wipeout'']] beginning in winter 2011.<ref>{{cite web|author=James Hibberd |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/06/16/wipeout-fifth-season/ |title='Wipeout' renewed for fifth season |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=2011-06-16 |accessdate=2016-12-26}}</ref> Her first appearance was on December 8, 2011. Due to her pregnancy, Lachey left the show in late 2012 and was replaced by [[Jill Wagner]].\n\nLachey has appeared in television series including ''That's Life'', ''City Girls'', ''30 Rock'', ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]'', ''[[Psych]]'', ''Hawaii 5-0'' and ''Maybe It's Me''. In 2008, she played Ashlee in the ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'' episode \"[[No Tomorrow (How I Met Your Mother)|No Tomorrow]]\".\nShe starred in the 2008 comedy ''[[Disaster Movie]]'', a [[parody|spoof]] of big-budget [[Hollywood]] [[Disaster film|disaster movies]]. Released on August 29, 2008, the film had moderate box office success, earning $34,624,652 worldwide. The film received extremely negative reviews, earning six [[Razzie]] Award nominations. It stands at number one on the [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]] Bottom 100.\n\nLachey (as Vanessa Minnillo) signed on to appear in ''Redefining Love'', a 2009 romantic comedy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starnewsonline.com/article/20080229/NEWS/802290334 |title=Minnillo signs on for Wilmington film |publisher=StarNewsOnline.com |date=2008-02-29 |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref> but she is not listed in the final cast.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1210097/fullcredits#cast Redefining Love at IMDb]</ref>\nIn November 2009, TVGuide.com announced that Minnillo would guest star alongside ''[[Disaster Movie]]'' co-star [[Kim Kardashian]] on [[CBS]]'s ''[[CSI: NY]]''. \"The ladies [Vanessa and Kim] portray two women who've managed to concoct a very interesting scheme that ends in murder,\" confirmed executive producer [[Pam Veasey]].<ref name=\"TV Guide\">{{cite news | author=Kate Stanhope | title= Kim Kardashian and Vanessa Minnillo to Appear on CSI:NY| url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Kardashian-Minnillo-CSI-1011580.aspx| work=TVGuide.com}}</ref> Minnillo's former [[MTV]] colleague and close friend, [[La La Vasquez]], as well as the band Train, also appeared in the episode.<ref name=\"TV Guide\"/>\nIn 2011, she guest starred on ''[[30 Rock]]'' as Carmen Chao, Avery's coworker at NBC who is competing for the same promotion. Minnillo later guest starred on the then-new series ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'' with then fianc\u00e9 [[Nick Lachey]].\n\nOn September 6, 2017, Lachey was announced as one of the celebrities who will take part on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 25)|25th season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'', competing against her husband Nick. She was paired with professional dancer [[Maksim Chmerkovskiy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-season-25-celebrity-cast-frankie-muniz/story?id=49603734|title='Dancing With the Stars' season 25 celebrity cast: Frankie Muniz, Barbara Corcoran, Nick Lachey and more|work=ABC News|date=September 6, 2017|accessdate=September 6, 2017}}</ref>  Chmerkovskiy's wife, [[Peta Murgatroyd]], was paired with Nick. On October 30, Lachey and Chmerkovskiy became the seventh couple to be eliminated from the competition, finishing in joint seventh place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/10/31/dancing-stars-who-went-home-shocking-double-elimination/816260001/|title='Dancing with the Stars': Who went home in the shocking double-elimination?|work=USA Today|date=October 31, 2017|accessdate=January 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMinnillo began dating singer [[Nick Lachey]] in 2006 (prior to his separation from [[Jessica Simpson]] in December the following year and divorced later at the end of June in the same year) after they met when she appeared in the music video for his song \"[[What's Left of Me (song)|What's Left of Me]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1651572/20101104/lachey_nick.jhtml|title=Nick Lachey And Vanessa Minnillo Are Engaged |date=2010-11-04|publisher=mtv.com|accessdate=2010-11-15}}</ref> In June 2009, they broke up,<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20287060,00.html|title=Nick Lachey and Vanessa Minnillo Split|date=2009-06-23|magazine=People|accessdate=2010-11-15}}</ref> but in October 2009, Lachey confirmed that they were back together after having been \"single for a minute\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20311200,00.html|title=Nick Lachey & Vanessa Minnillo: Back On!|date=2009-06-23|magazine=People|accessdate=2009-10-08|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091010012642/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20311200,00.html|archivedate=2009-10-10}}</ref> Minnillo and Lachey became engaged in November 2010.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20439700,00.html|title=Vanessa Minnillo & Nick Lachey Are Engaged!|date=2010-11-04|magazine=People|accessdate=2010-11-15}}</ref>\n\nThe couple married on July 15, 2011 at Sir [[Richard Branson]]'s private [[Necker Island (British Virgin Islands)|Necker Island]] in the [[British Virgin Islands]].<ref>Garcia, Jennifer. [http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20511009,00.html \"Nick Lachey & Vanessa Minnillo: Why We Picked Necker Island for Wedding\"], ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'', July 18, 2011</ref> Nick and Vanessa Lachey have three children together.<ref>Michaud, Sarah and Garcia, Jennifer. [http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/09/13/nick-lachey-vanessa-lachey-welcome-son-camden-john/ \"Nick and Vanessa Lachey Welcome Son Camden John\"], ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'', September 13, 2012</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/vanessa-minnillo-welcomes-baby-girl-brooklyn-with-nick-lachey-pic-201561|title=Vanessa Minnillo Gives Birth, Welcomes Baby Girl Brooklyn Elisabeth With Nick Lachey: First Photo|date=January 6, 2015|work=Us Weekly|accessdate=January 18, 2015|first=Stephanie|last=Webber}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Vanessa Lachey |url=http://vanessalachey.com/2015/01/proud-parents-baby-girl-lachey-is-here/ |title=Proud Parents: Baby Girl Lachey is Here! |publisher=Vanessa Lachey |date=2015-01-06 |accessdate=2016-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Schnurr|first1=Samantha|title=Nick Lachey and Vanessa Lachey Expecting Baby No. 3|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/792013/nick-lachey-and-vanessa-lachey-expecting-baby-no-3|accessdate=September 3, 2016|work=[[E! Online]]|date=September 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Quinn|first1=Dave|title='A Christmas Miracle!' Nick and Vanessa Lachey Welcome Son Phoenix Robert|url=http://people.com/babies/nick-and-vanessa-lachey-welcome-son-phoenix-robert/?xid=socialflow_facebook_peoplemag|accessdate=December 26, 2016|work=[[People Magazine]]|date=December 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer]]''\n| Julie Angel\n| Credited as Johnny's Wedding Date; as Vanessa Minnillo\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Disaster Movie]]''\n| Amy\n| as Vanessa Minnillo\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[That's Life (2000 TV series)|That's Life]]''\n| Cheerleader\n| Episode: \"Oh, Crap!\"; as Vanessa Minnillo\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[City Guys]]''\n| Hot Girl\n| Episode: \"Dances with Malcolm\"; as Vanessa Minnillo\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]''\n| Amanda Wexler\n| Recurring role; 8 episodes, as Vanessa Minnillo\n|-\n| 200